Package edu.umass.cs.surveyman.survey

Class edu.umass.cs.surveyman.survey.Block extends SurveyObj implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

strId

String strId
The source identifier

sourceLines

List<E> sourceLines
The line numbers in the source file associated with this block.

questions

List<E> questions
The questions that reside directly in this block (not in sub-blocks).

branchQ

Question branchQ
The branch question associated with this block. If the branch question is derived from an ALL block, this is just set to an arbitrary question within that block. It is used for debugging purposes.

branchParadigm

Block.BranchParadigm branchParadigm
The branch paradigm associated with this block.

subBlocks

List<E> subBlocks
The sub-blocks that this block contains.

parentBlock

Block parentBlock
The parent pointer for this block. This is null if the block is top-level.

randomize

boolean randomize
Boolean indicating whether this block is floating.

id

int[] id
The internal block representation; used for sorting, suffling, and generating "phantom" blocks.

Class edu.umass.cs.surveyman.survey.Question extends SurveyObj implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

quid

String quid
Unique question identifier. Typically generated upon parsing.

data

Component data
Data to be displayed when the user takes the survye.

answer

Component answer
Answer to the question, if it exists.

options

Map<K,V> options
Map from component identifiers to answer option objects (Component).

branchMap

BranchMap branchMap
Map from answer options to branch destinations (Block). This may be left empty if there is no branching.

sourceLineNos

List<E> sourceLineNos
Source data line numbers corresponding to this question. Used for parsing and debugging.

otherValues

Map<K,V> otherValues
Map from other input column headers to their values, when they exist for this question.

block

Block block
The enclosing block for this question.

exclusive

Boolean exclusive
True if respondents may only answer one of the answer options.

ordered

Boolean ordered
True if the answer options have a natural ordering (e.g., Likert scales).

randomize

Boolean randomize
True if the answer options may be randomized. If the ordered field is true, then there are only two possible permutations. If the ordered field is false, there are factorial permutations in the number of options.

freetext

Boolean freetext
True if this question requires a text response.

freetextPattern

Pattern freetextPattern
Set if this question requires a text response and must conform to a regular expression.

freetextDefault

String freetextDefault
Set if this question requires a text response and should display example text.

permitBreakoff

boolean permitBreakoff
Indicates whether respondents may submit their results immediately after answering this questions, regardless of its position in the survey.

correlation

String correlation
A correlation label.

correlationMap
